  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to the Facilitation of Forest Governance Reforms in Guyana, Liberia, Ghana, Republic of Congo and Cameroon (FLEGT)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this contract is to establish and operate a Facilitation service that helps sustain and support national stakeholders so that they input and inform forest sector governance reforms as framed by the Voluntary Partnership Agreements in Ghana, Liberia, Republic of Congo, Cameroon, Guyana, and Gabon. Facilitation support will improve the quality of national deliberation, encouraging inclusion of different stakeholder interests, helping clarify misunderstandings and promoting lesson learning and thereby helping to establish a strong foundation for lasting transformation in the ways forests are governed and managed. This will help build local ownership for VPA results in each country where the Facilitators are deployed. The Facilitation Service will contribute to FGMC programme-wide monitoring and lesson learning and assist in the coordination of FGMC action at the country level to improve programme effectiveness.</narrative>
  </description>
